§ Result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Suppose $x: Ω → 𝗥^d$ has normal density $g: 𝗥^d → 𝗥$ on
    probability space $(Ω, 𝒜, 𝗣)$. ⦉

  ‖ Suppose $x$ has mean $μ ∈ 𝗥^d$ and covariance $Σ ≻ 0$. ⦉

  ‖ Then the entropy of $x$ is
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ h(g) = -∫ g \log g = \frac{1}{2} \log ((2πe)^d \det Σ) ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ This result tells us the ❬multivariate normal entropy❭ (or
    ❬Gaussian entropy❭). ⦉
